 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search IT Manager Text IQ New York State Remote Text IQ is a B2B Artificial Intelligence company with a reimagined approach to managing and mitigating risks derived from enterprise data. Text IQ's Unstructured Data Platform uses AI to help Global 2000s and government agencies around the world protect sensitive information with ease and speed, providing the freedom to grow. 
 
Since its founding in 2014, Text IQ has achieved record growth in revenue. Featured in TechCrunch and Forbes, Text IQ's AI solutions have been implemented at some of the world's leading financial services, insurance, healthcare and government organizations and has the backing of executives from Bank of America, Goldman Sachs, Verizon, Oracle, and Apple in addition to top venture capital firms including FirstMark Capital, Sierra Ventures, and Floodgate. 
 
We're looking for a skilled IT Manager to join our team to build and support essential systems, tools, and infrastructure to propel Text IQ's growth. Responsibilities will include developing and implementing hardware and software as well as providing stellar end-user support. The ideal candidate has a background in software and hardware troubleshooting, enjoys supporting systems with a focus on automation and security, is passionate about IT end-user support, and should be eager to build our IT support from the ground up. 
 
As an IT Manager, you will: 
 
 Own the full life cycle (procurement, maintenance, inventory, and disposal) of company IT assets (i.e. laptop, tablets, phones, network equipment, etc.) 
 Ensure IT asset compliance with applicable security standards 
 Build an auto-provisioning framework for day to day IT support tasks 
 Be an integral part of the onboarding and off-boarding processes 
 Collaborate within cross functional teams such as InfoSec and DevOps teams 
 Grow and scale Text IQ's IT engineering program 
 Provide technical support to all employees 
 Own and maintain the corporate VPN solutions 
 Maintain and provide support for IT infrastructure access requirements 
 Troubleshoot issues and access requests 
 Provide guidance and opportunities to other members of the team 
 Apply industry best practices in all aspects of job responsibilities 
 
 We are looking for Teammates who have: 
 
 3+ years of experience in an IT support role 
 1+ year of experience managing or leading other IT professionals 
 Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills 
 A strong "everyone is responsible for security" mindset 
 Experience writing automation code to provision hardware 
 Sense of ownership for issue resolution, including escalating critical issues to senior management and staff when necessary 
 Excellent customer-focused interaction and dedication to delivering optimal service 
 Ability and confidence to write code/scripts to automate work 
 Consistency in delivering value in a timely manner 
 Understands the need to provide team metrics & KPIs 
 
 We'd particularly love it if you: 
 
 Are experienced with OpenVPN 
 Have cursory understanding of AWS 
 Have distributed work experience 
 Can effectively make decisions in a fast-paced, challenging environment 
 
 We'd be truly impressed if you: 
 
 Have experience with Ansible or Terraform 
 Can work with Docker 
 Are motivated to grow the IT team into a world-class department 
 
 At Text IQ, we believe that our team members are the most critical building block of our success. When you join Text IQ, you join a people-centric culture where you will have the opportunity to work with some of the leading companies in the world, and the most talented people in the industry. We invest in talented people and give them room to grow and innovate. 
 
We believe every Text IQ team member has a right to affordable healthcare, retirement, vacation, and other company perks. Our People team is constantly coming up with new ideas to support our people's health, happiness and professional development. We offer a comprehensive with benefits package, including: 
 
 Discretionary Unlimited PTO 
 Fun, diverse, open-minded coworkers 
 High level of autonomy 
 Training, mentorship, and coaching from leadership 
 Company-paid health & dental insurance with optional vision, life, and disability choices 
 Working From Home Stipend 
 Annual Bonus Opportunity 
 Referral bonus 
 
 Text IQ is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We do not discriminate against qualified applicants or employees on the basis of race, color, religion, gender identity, sex, sexual preference, sexual identity, pregnancy, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, marital status, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, military status, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local law, rule, or regulation. 
 
